article.headline: Tennessee Tech 65, Morehead St. 52
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Amadi McKenzie had game highs with 14 points and eight rebounds to help Tennessee Tech beat Morehead State 65-52 on Monday night. Tennessee Tech (13-9, 9-4 Ohio Valley Conference), winning its seventh straight, was tied five times and fell behind twice in the first eight minutes, but had a 15-7 run to go ahead 27-18 with 5:40 left in the half. Morehead State (10-11, 6-7) was cold the whole night, shooting 29 percent from the field. The Eagles fell behind 37-24 at the half and never recovered. Anthony Fisher added 12 points, including 8-of-10 from the line, and six rebounds for the Golden Eagles, who hit 50 percent from the field. Quentin Pryor led Morehead with 12 points and six rebounds. Brandon Callahan got an indirect technical foul for dunking during pre-game warmups.
